verses.verse: The LORD <WH3068> reigneth, <WH4427> he is clothed <WH3847> with majesty; <WH1348> the LORD <WH3068> is clothed <WH3847> with strength, <WH5797> wherewith he hath girded himself: <WH247> the world <WH8398> also <WH637> is established, <WH3559> that it cannot <WH1077> be moved. <WH4131>
Thy throne <WH3678> is established <WH3559> of old: <WH4480> <WH227> thou <WH859> art from everlasting. <WH4480> <WH5769>
The floods <WH5104> have lifted up, <WH5375> O LORD, <WH3068> the floods <WH5104> have lifted up <WH5375> their voice; <WH6963> the floods <WH5104> lift up <WH5375> their waves. <WH1796>
The LORD <WH3068> on high <WH4791> is mightier <WH117> than the noise <WH4480> <WH6963> of many <WH7227> waters, <WH4325> yea, than the mighty <WH117> waves <WH4867> of the sea. <WH3220>
Thy testimonies <WH5713> are very <WH3966> sure: <WH539> holiness <WH6944> becometh <WH4998> thine house, <WH1004> O LORD, <WH3068> forever. <WH753> <WH3117>
